    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once all of the vegetables are tender, boil a kettle</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Remove the skins and roots from your<strong> onion</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and discard, then add them to a<strong> food processor</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and all of the <strong>softened vegetables</strong></p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>milk </strong>and whizz until smooth – this is your <strong>parsnip soup</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
